links.title: Why These Social Media Stocks Are Trading Higher Today
links.description: Shares of several social media companies are trading higher in sympathy with Snap Inc. (NYSE: SNAP) after the company reported strong third-quarter earnings results. Snap also reported daily active users grew by 18% year-over-year. Twitter, Inc. (NYSE: TWTR) was trading up 8.33% at $50.21 per share on Wednesday at the time of publication.
